uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "1.11", "subsection_index": 10, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "1.12, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "1.12 A party seeking an order for disclosure in a Part 8 claim shall serve and file a List of Issues for Disclosure in relation to which disclosure is sought and the Models that are to be adopted for each issue. The court may adapt the provisions of this Practice Direction in such manner as may be appropriate when making an order for disclosure in a Part 8 claim. SECTION I 2. Principles, "document", "adverse" and "known adverse documents"", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_11", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "1.12", "subsection_index": 11, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.1 Disclosure is important in achieving the fair resolution of civil proceedings. It involves identifying and making available documents that are relevant to the issues in the proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_12", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.1", "subsection_index": 12, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.2 For the purpose of disclosure, the term "document" includes any record of any description containing information. The term is further defined below.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_13", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.2", "subsection_index": 13, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.3 The court expects the parties (and their representatives) to cooperate with each other and to assist the court so that the scope of disclosure, if any, that is required in proceedings can be agreed or determined by the court in the most efficient way possible.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_14", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.3", "subsection_index": 14, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.4 The court will be concerned to ensure that disclosure is directed to the issues in the proceedings and that the scope of disclosure is not wider than is reasonable and proportionate (as defined in paragraph 6.4) in order fairly to resolve those issues, and specifically the Issues for Disclosure (as defined in paragraph 7.6).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_15", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.4", "subsection_index": 15, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.5 A "document" may take any form including but not limited to paper or electronic; it may be held by computer or on portable devices such as memory sticks or mobile phones or within databases; it includes e-mail and other electronic communications such as text messages, webmail, social media and voicemail, audio or visual recordings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_16", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.5", "subsection_index": 16, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.6, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.6 In addition to information that is readily accessible from computer systems and other electronic devices and media, the term "document" extends to information that is stored on servers and back-up systems and electronic information that has been 'deleted'. It also extends to metadata, and other embedded data which is not typically visible on screen or a printout.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_17", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.6", "subsection_index": 17, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.7, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.7 Disclosure extends to "adverse" documents. A document is "adverse" if it or any information it contains contradicts or materially damages the disclosing party's contention or version of events on an issue in dispute, or supports the contention or version of events of an opposing party on an issue in dispute, whether or not that issue is one of the agreed Issues for Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_18", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.7", "subsection_index": 18, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.8, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.8"Known adverse documents" are documents (other than privileged documents) that a party is actually aware (without undertaking any further search for documents than it has already undertaken or caused to be undertaken) both (a) are or were previously within its control and (b) are adverse.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_19", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.8", "subsection_index": 19, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.9, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "2.9 For this purpose a company or organisation is "aware" if any person with accountability or responsibility within the company or organisation for the events or the circumstances which are the subject of the case, or for the conduct of the proceedings, is aware. For this purpose it is also necessary to take reasonable steps to check the position with any person who has had such accountability or responsibility but who has since left the company or organisation. 3. Duties in relation to disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_20", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "2.9", "subsection_index": 20, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "3.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "3.1 A person who knows that it is or may become a party to proceedings that have been commenced or who knows that it may become a party to proceedings that may be commenced is under the following duties ("the Disclosure Duties") to the court-

(1) to take reasonable steps to preserve documents in its control that may be relevant to any issue in the proceedings;

(2) by no later than the time(s) set out in paragraphs 9.1 to 9.3, to disclose known adverse documents, unless they are privileged. This duty exists regardless of whether or not any order for disclosure is made;

(3) to comply with any order for disclosure made by the court;

(4) to undertake any search for documents in a responsible and conscientious manner to fulfil the stated purpose of the search;

(5) to act honestly in relation to the process of giving disclosure and reviewing documents disclosed by the other party; and

(6) to use reasonable efforts to avoid providing documents to another party that have no relevance to the Issues for Disclosure in the proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_21", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "3.1", "subsection_index": 21, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "3.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "3.2 Legal representatives who have the conduct of litigation on behalf of a party to proceedings that have been commenced, or who are instructed with a view to the conduct of litigation where their client knows it may become a party to proceedings that have been or may be commenced, are under the following duties to the court-

(1) to take reasonable steps to preserve documents within their control that may be relevant to any issue in the proceedings;

(2) to take reasonable steps to advise and assist the party to comply with its Disclosure Duties;

(3) to liaise and cooperate with the legal representatives of the other parties to the proceedings (or the other parties where they do not have legal representatives) so as to promote the reliable, efficient and cost-effective conduct of disclosure, including through the use of technology;

(4) to act honestly in relation to the process of giving disclosure and reviewing documents disclosed by the other party; and

(5) to undertake a review to satisfy themselves that any claim by the party to privilege from disclosing a document is properly made and the reason for the claim to privilege is sufficiently explained.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_22", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "3.2", "subsection_index": 22, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "3.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "3.3 The duties under paragraphs 3.1 and 3.2 above are continuing duties that last until the conclusion of the proceedings (including any appeal) or until it is clear there will be no proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_23", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "3.3", "subsection_index": 23, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "3.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "3.4 Where there is a known adverse document but it has not been located, the duty to disclose the document is met by that fact being disclosed, subject to any further order that the court may make. 4. Preservation of documents", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_24", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "3.4", "subsection_index": 24, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.1 Documents to be preserved in accordance with the duties under paragraphs 3.1(1) and 3.2(1) above include documents which might otherwise be deleted or destroyed in accordance with a document retention policy or in the ordinary course of business. Preservation includes, in suitable cases, making copies of sources and documents and storing them.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_25", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.1", "subsection_index": 25, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.2 The duty under paragraph 3.1(1) and 3.2(1) includes-

(1) an obligation to suspend relevant document deletion or destruction processes for the duration of the proceedings;

(2) in accordance with paragraph 4.3 below, an obligation to send a written notification in any form to relevant employees and former employees of the party where there are reasonable grounds for believing that the employee or former employee may be in possession of disclosable documents which are not also in the party's possession; and

(3) an obligation to take reasonable steps so that agents or third parties who may hold documents on the party's behalf do not delete or destroy documents that may be relevant to an issue in the proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_26", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.2", "subsection_index": 26, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.3 A written notification under paragraph 4.2 above should-

(1) identify the documents or classes of documents to be preserved; and

(2) notify the recipient that they should not delete or destroy those documents and should take reasonable steps to preserve them.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_27", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.3", "subsection_index": 27, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.4 Legal representatives who have the conduct of litigation on behalf of a party to proceedings that have been commenced, or who are instructed with a view to the conduct of litigation where their client knows it may become a party to proceedings that have been or may be commenced, must within a reasonable period of being instructed-

(1) notify their client of the need to preserve documents and of their obligations under paragraph 3.1 above; and

(2) obtain written confirmation from their client or an appropriate representative of their client that their client has taken the steps required under paragraphs 4.2 and 4.3 above.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_28", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.4", "subsection_index": 28, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "4.5 Each party must confirm in writing (and may do so by their legal representative) when serving their particulars of claim or defence (as appropriate), that steps have been taken to preserve relevant documents in accordance with the duties under paragraph 3.1(1) and 3.2(1) above, and as required by paragraph 4.1 to 4.4 above. 5. Initial Disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_29", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "4.5", "subsection_index": 29, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.1 Save as provided below, and save in the case of a Part 7 claim form without particulars of claim, each party must provide to all other parties at the same time as its statement of case an Initial Disclosure List of Documents that lists and is accompanied by copies of-

(1) the key documents on which it has relied (expressly or otherwise) in support of the claims or defences advanced in its statement of case (and including the documents referred to in that statement of case); and

(2) the key documents that are necessary to enable the other parties to understand the claim or defence they have to meet.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_30", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.1", "subsection_index": 30, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.2 This form of disclosure is known as "Initial Disclosure".", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_31", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.2", "subsection_index": 31, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.3 Initial Disclosure is not required where-

(1) the parties have agreed to dispense with it (see paragraph 5.8 below);

(2) the court has ordered that it is not required (see paragraph 5.10 below); or

(3) a party concludes and states in writing, approaching the matter in good faith, that giving Initial Disclosure would involve it or any other party providing (after removing duplicates, and including documents referred to at paragraph 5.4(3)(a)) more than (about) whichever is the larger of 1000 pages or 200 documents (or such higher but reasonable figure as the parties may agree), at which point the requirement to give Initial Disclosure ceases for all parties for the purposes of the case.

Documents comprising media not in page form are not included in the calculation of the page or document limit at (3) but, where provided pursuant to a requirement to give Initial Disclosure, should be confined strictly to what is necessary to comply with paragraph 5.1 above.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_32", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.3", "subsection_index": 32, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.4 A party giving Initial Disclosure-

(1) is under no obligation to undertake a search for documents beyond any search it has already undertaken or caused to be undertaken for the purposes of the proceedings (including in advance of the commencement of the proceedings);

(2) need not provide unless requested documents by way of Initial Disclosure if such documents-

(a) have already been provided to the other party, whether by disclosure before proceedings start (see CPR 31.16) or through pre-action correspondence or otherwise in the period following intimation of the proceedings (and including when giving Initial Disclosure with a statement of case that is being amended); or

(b) are known to be or have been in the other party's possession;

(3) need not disclose adverse documents by way of Initial Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_33", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.4", "subsection_index": 33, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.5 Unless otherwise ordered, or agreed between the parties, copies of documents shall be provided in electronic form for the purpose of Initial Disclosure. The Initial Disclosure List of Documents should be filed but the documents must not be filed.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_34", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.5", "subsection_index": 34, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.6, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.6 In proceedings where a statement of case is to be served on a defendant out of the jurisdiction Initial Disclosure is not required in respect of that defendant unless and until that defendant files an acknowledgement of service that does not contest the jurisdiction, or files a further acknowledgement of service under CPR 11(7)(b).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_35", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.6", "subsection_index": 35, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.7, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.7 For the avoidance of doubt, Initial Disclosure does not require any document to be translated.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_36", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.7", "subsection_index": 36, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.8, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.8 The parties may agree in writing, before or after the commencement of proceedings, to dispense with, or defer, Initial Disclosure. They may also agree to dispense with the requirement to produce an Initial Disclosure List of Documents. Each party should record its respective reasons for any agreement, so that those reasons may be available to the court, on request, at any case management conference. The court may set aside an agreement to dispense with or defer Initial Disclosure if it considers that Initial Disclosure is likely to provide significant benefits and the costs of providing Initial Disclosure are unlikely to be disproportionate to such benefits.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_37", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.8", "subsection_index": 37, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.9, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.9 The court shall disregard any prior agreement to dispense with Initial Disclosure when considering whether to order Extended Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_38", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.9", "subsection_index": 38, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.10, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.10 A party may apply to the court for directions limiting or abrogating the obligation to provide Initial Disclosure. In particular, if a party is requested but does not agree to dispense with Initial Disclosure, the requesting party may apply to the court with notice to the other party for directions limiting or abrogating the obligation to provide Initial Disclosure if it considers compliance with the obligation will incur disproportionate cost or be unduly complex. Such an application must be made by application notice, supported by evidence where necessary, and, save in exceptional cases, will be dealt with without a hearing or at a short telephone hearing.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_39", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.10", "subsection_index": 39, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.11, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.11 In an appropriate case the court may, on application, and whether or not Initial Disclosure has been given, require a party to disclose documents to another party where that is necessary to enable the other party to understand the claim or defence they have to meet or to formulate a defence or a reply.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_40", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.11", "subsection_index": 40, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.12, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.12 A complaint about Initial Disclosure shall be dealt with at the first case management conference unless, exceptionally and on application, the court considers that the issue should be resolved at an earlier hearing.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_41", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.12", "subsection_index": 41, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.13, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.13 A significant failure to comply with the obligation to provide Initial Disclosure may be taken into account by the court when considering whether to make an order for Extended Disclosure and the terms of such an order. It may also result in an adverse order for costs.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_42", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.13", "subsection_index": 42, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "5.14, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "5.14 For the avoidance of doubt, nothing in this paragraph affects the operation of paragraph 7.3 of Practice Direction 16. 6. Extended Disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_43", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "5.14", "subsection_index": 43, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.1 A party wishing to seek disclosure of documents in addition to, or as an alternative to, Initial Disclosure must request Extended Disclosure. No application notice is required. However, the parties will be expected to have completed the Disclosure Review Document pursuant to paragraphs 7 and following below.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_44", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.1", "subsection_index": 44, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.2 Save where otherwise provided, Extended Disclosure involves using Disclosure Models (see paragraph 8 below) in respect of Issues for Disclosure which have been identified (see paragraph 7 below).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_45", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.2", "subsection_index": 45, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.3 The court will only make an order for Extended Disclosure that is search-based (ie Models C, D and/or E) where it is persuaded that it is appropriate to do so in order fairly to resolve one or more of the Issues for Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_46", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.3", "subsection_index": 46, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.4 In all cases, an order for Extended Disclosure must be reasonable and proportionate having regard to the overriding objective including the following factors-

(1) the nature and complexity of the issues in the proceedings;

(2) the importance of the case, including any non-monetary relief sought;

(3) the likelihood of documents existing that will have probative value in supporting or undermining a party's claim or defence;

(4) the number of documents involved;

(5) the ease and expense of searching for and retrieval of any particular document (taking into account any limitations on the information available and on the likely accuracy of any costs estimates);

(6) the financial position of each party; and

(7) the need to ensure the case is dealt with expeditiously, fairly and at a proportionate cost.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_47", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.4", "subsection_index": 47, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.5 A request for search-based Extended Disclosure (ie Models C, D and/or E) must specify which of the Disclosure Models listed in paragraph 8 below is proposed for each Issue for Disclosure defined in paragraph 7 below. It is for the party requesting Extended Disclosure to show that what is sought is appropriate, reasonable and proportionate (as defined in paragraph 6.4).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_48", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.5", "subsection_index": 48, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.6, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.6 The objective of relating Disclosure Models to Issues for Disclosure is to limit the searches required and the volume of documents to be disclosed. Issues for Disclosure may be grouped. Disclosure Models should not be used in a way that increases cost through undue complexity.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_49", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.6", "subsection_index": 49, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.7, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.7 It is important that the parties consider what types of documents and sources of documents there are or may be, including what documents another party is likely to have, in order that throughout a realistic approach may be taken to disclosure.

Court control over disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_50", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.7", "subsection_index": 50, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.8, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.8 The court will determine whether to order Extended Disclosure at the first case management conference or, if directed by the court, at another hearing convened for that purpose or without a hearing.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_51", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.449289560317993, "score": 0.019833087921142578, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", 