Case management in the Royal Courts of Justice", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_0", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "1.1", "subsection_index": 0, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.1, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "2.1 This part of the practice direction applies to claims begun by claim form issued in the Central Office or Chancery Chambers in the Royal Courts of Justice.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_1", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "2.1", "subsection_index": 1, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.2, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "2.2 A claim with an estimated value of less than 100,000 will generally, unless:

(a) it is required by an enactment to be tried in the High Court,

(b) it falls within a specialist list, or

(c) it falls within one of the categories specified in 2.6 below or is otherwise within the criteria of article 7(5) of the High Court and County Courts Jurisdiction Order 1991,

be transferred to a county court.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_2", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "2.2", "subsection_index": 2, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.3, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "2.3 Paragraph 2.2 is without prejudice to the power of the court in accordance with Part 30 to transfer to a county court a claim with an estimated value that exceeds 100,000.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_3", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "2.3", "subsection_index": 3, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.4, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "2.4 The decision to transfer may be made at any stage in the proceedings but should, subject to paragraph 2.5, be made as soon as possible and in any event not later than the date for the filing of pre-trial check lists (listing questionnaires).", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_4", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "2.4", "subsection_index": 4, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.5, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "2.5 If an application is made under rule 3.4 (striking out) or under Part 24 (summary judgment) or under Part 25 (interim remedies), it will usually be convenient for the application to be dealt with before a decision to transfer is taken.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_5", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "2.5", "subsection_index": 5, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.6, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "2.6 Each party should state in his directions questionnaire whether he considers the claim should be managed and tried at the Royal Courts of Justice and, if so, why. Claims suitable for trial in the Royal Courts of Justice include:

(1) professional negligence claims,

(2) Fatal Accident Act claims,

(3) fraud or undue influence claims,

(4) defamation claims,

(5) claims for malicious prosecution or false imprisonment,

(6) claims against the police,

(7) contentious probate claims.

Such claims may fall within the criteria of article 7(5) of the High Court and County Courts Jurisdiction Order 1991.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_6", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "2.6", "subsection_index": 6, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.6, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "2.6 AIf the claim falls within a specialist list or area of work (i.e. Chancery, Commercial/Mercantile, or TCC), and concerns a dispute arising in a region outside London, the parties are required to explain in their directions questionnaire how and why the case is not suitable to be heard in the appropriate regional specialist court. Those regional specialist court centres have been set up to deal with appropriate cases out of London, so the parties will need to state in detail why, despite the availability of a regional specialist court, they wish the case to be heard in London.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_7", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "2.6", "subsection_index": 7, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "2.7, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "2.7 Attention is drawn to Practice Direction 30.

