n 29", "content": "4.4 The court may have regard to any document filed by a party with his directions questionnaire containing further information, provided that the document states either that its contents has been agreed with every other party or that it has been served on every other party, and when it was served.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_22", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "4.4", "subsection_index": 22, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.5, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "4.5 On the allocation of a claim to the multi-track the court will consider whether it is desirable or necessary to hold a case management conference straight away, or whether it is appropriate instead to give directions on its own initiative.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_23", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "4.5", "subsection_index": 23, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.6, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "4.6 Attention is drawn to rule 29.4, which provides that parties must endeavour to agree appropriate directions for the management of the proceedings, and requires the agreed directions or proposals to be submitted to the court within a specified time period.", "filepath": "Practice Direction 29", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_29_subsection_24", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_29", "reranker_score": 2.4273126125335693, "score": 0.014705882407724857, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 29", "sourcepage": "Practice Direction 29", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29", "subsection_id": "4.6", "subsection_index": 24, "total_subsections": 64, "updated": "2017-01-30T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part29/pd_part29"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "4.7, Practice Direction 29, Practice Direction 29", "content": "4.7

(1) To obtain the court's approval the agreed directions must -

(a) set out a timetable by reference to calendar dates for the taking of steps for the preparation of the case,

(b) include a date or a period (the trial period) when it is proposed that the trial will take place,

(c) include provision about disclosure of documents, and

(d) include provision about both factual and expert evidence.

(2) The court will scrutinise the timetable carefully and in particular will be concerned to see that any proposed date or period for the trial and (if provided for) for a case management conference is no later than is reasonably necessary.

(3) The provision in (1)(c) above may -

(a) limit disclosure to standard disclosure or less than that, and/or

(b) direct that disclosure will take place by the supply of copy documents without a list, but it must in that case say either that the parties must serve a disclosure statement with the copies or that they have agreed to disclose in that way without such a statement.

