-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.9", "subsection_index": 52, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.10, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.10 The court may also provide disclosure guidance in accordance with paragraph 11.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_53", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.10", "subsection_index": 53, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "6.11, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "6.11 Upon the application of the parties/a party, or on its own motion, the court may vary any period of time for a party/the parties to complete a step in disclosure. If the variation is agreed between the parties and will not affect the date set for the Case Management Conference or trial (as appropriate), court approval is not required. 7. Identifying the Issues for Disclosure", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_54", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "6.11", "subsection_index": 54, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.1, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.1 Within 28 days of the final statement of case each party should state, in writing, whether or not it is likely to request search-based Extended Disclosure to include one or more of Models C, D or E (see paragraph 8 below) on one or more Issues for Disclosure in the case. At this point it should not particularise the Model(s) or the issue(s) in the case.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_55", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.1", "subsection_index": 55, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.2, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.2 Where one or more of the parties has indicated it is likely to request search-based Extended Disclosure (i.e. Models C, D and/or E), the claimant must within 42 days of the final statement of case prepare and serve on the other parties a draft List of Issues for Disclosure unless an agreed list of issues for trial already exists and the parties agree that it is suitable (with or without adaptation) to be used for disclosure. The draft List of Issues for Disclosure should be set out in Section 1 A of the Disclosure Review Document.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_56", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.2", "subsection_index": 56, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.3, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.3 At the same time as serving a draft List of Issues for Disclosure, the claimant shall identify for each Issue for Disclosure which Model of Extended Disclosure it proposes for each party. If the claimant proposes Model C Disclosure for any Issue for Disclosure it should indicate, using Section 1 B of the Disclosure Review Document, how the particular documents or narrow class of documents it proposes should be defined for that purpose (see paragraph 8 below).", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_57", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.3", "subsection_index": 57, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.4, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.4 If the claimant fails to prepare and serve a List of Issues for Disclosure within 42 days of the final statement of case any defendant may prepare and serve its own draft List of Issues for Disclosure on the other parties together with its proposed Models including any Model C requests.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_58", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.4", "subsection_index": 58, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.5, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.5 A List of Issues for Disclosure is not required if the parties are agreed that Extended Disclosure is to be confined to Models A and B.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_59", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.5", "subsection_index": 59, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.6, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.6 The List of Issues for Disclosure should be as short and concise as possible. "Issues for Disclosure" means for the purposes of disclosure only those key issues in dispute, which the parties consider will need to be determined by the court with some reference to contemporaneous documents in order for there to be a fair resolution of the proceedings. It does not extend to every issue which is disputed in the statements of case by denial or non-admission. For the purposes of producing a List of Issues for Disclosure the parties should consider what matters are common ground but should only include the key issues in dispute in the list.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_60", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.6", "subsection_index": 60, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.7, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.7 When drafting Issues for Disclosure the parties should have regard to the primary functions of those Issues namely (i) to help the parties to consider, and the court to determine, whether Extended Disclosure is required and, if so, which Model or Models should be used; (ii) to assist the parties in identifying documents and categories of documents that are likely to exist and require to be disclosed; (iii) to assist those carrying out the disclosure process to do so in a practical and proportionate way including, in the case of search-based disclosure, to help define and guide the searches; (iv) to assist with the process of reviewing documents produced by searches; and (v) to avoid the production of documents that are not relevant to the issues in the proceedings.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_61", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.7", "subsection_index": 61, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.8, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.8 The claimant should seek to ensure that the draft List of Issues for Disclosure provides a fair and balanced summary of the key areas of dispute identified by the parties' statements of case and in respect of which it is likely that one or other of the parties will be seeking search-based Extended Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_62", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.8", "subsection_index": 62, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.9, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.9 A party served with a draft List of Issues for Disclosure and proposals on Models shall, as soon as practicable but in any event no later than 21 days from service, indicate using Section 1 A (and, if applicable, 1 B) of the Disclosure Review Document whether it agrees with the proposals (including any proposals as to how Model C Disclosure should be defined). If the party served with the proposals does not agree, or wishes to propose alternative or additional Issues for Disclosure, other Models and/or other Model C proposals, it should set out its alternative or additional proposals in Sections 1 A and 1 B of the Disclosure Review Document.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_63", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.9", "subsection_index": 63, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.10, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.10 In advance of the first case management conference, the parties must discuss and seek to agree the draft List of Issues for Disclosure, the Models identified for each Issue for Disclosure, and the wording of any Model C proposals. They should consider whether any draft Issue for Disclosure can be removed.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_64", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.10", "subsection_index": 64, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.11, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.11 Whilst reasonable and proportionate efforts are required to agree the List of Issues for Disclosure, if agreement cannot be reached after such efforts the List should be concluded by showing the areas of disagreement. The parties should consider seeking Disclosure Guidance from the court at an early stage as a means to help resolve the differences between them. One situation in which Disclosure Guidance should be considered is where one party believes the other is proposing a list of issues that is far too complex to serve as a List of Issues for Disclosure.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_65", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.11", "subsection_index": 65, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "Civil Procedure Rules and Practice Directions", "citation": "7.12, Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts, Practice Direction 57A", "content": "7.12 The List of Issues for Disclosure does not bind the parties at trial. The List of Issues for Disclosure need not contain / include a list of all the issues in the case and the issues in the case may develop or be refined as the case proceeds. The List of Issues for Disclosure may be revised or supplemented at any time prior to or following the case management conference, including as a result of statements of case or amended statements of case subsequently served or discussions between the parties in relation to the Disclosure Review Document.", "filepath": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "groups": [], "id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001_subsection_66", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "Practice_Direction_57AD___Disclosure_for_the_Business_and_Property_Courts_chunk_001", "reranker_score": 2.6706557273864746, "score": 0.022727273404598236, "sourcefile": "Practice Direction 57A", "sourcepage": "Disclosure for the Business and Property Courts", "storageUrl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "storageurl": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts", "subsection_id": "7.12", "subsection_index": 66, "total_subsections": 67, "updated": "2022-09-29T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.justice.gov.uk/courts/procedure-rules/civil/rules/part-57a-business-and-property-courts/practice-direction-57ad-disclosure-in-the-business-and-property-courts"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.2, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.2 Under CPR25.1 the court has power to grant various interim remedies, and applications for these are dealt with in Section 12 below. Under CPR25.2 the court can grant interim remedies before proceedings are started, and without notice having been given to the other party, but this is subject to various conditions.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_0", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.2", "subsection_index": 0, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.3, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.3 A High Court Judge is available on every day that the court is sitting both in normal hours and out of hours to deal with applications for interim remedies. Applications should be made to the Interim Applications Judge (who normally sits in Court 37). The practice and procedure is set out in paragraphs 9.55 to 9.61 and section 11.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_1", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.3", "subsection_index": 1, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.4, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.4 Masters have jurisdiction to grant various interim remedies, other than freezing and search orders (see PD2B paragraph 2). However, all applications for interim injunctions should be made to a High Court Judge.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_2", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.4", "subsection_index": 2, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.5, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.5 Applications are required to approve interim payments in claims involving children and protected parties. Those interim payments may be made at a time when a claim would not normally be issued. In those cases, a Part 8 claim should be issued, and any further applications for interim payments made in the Part 8 claim. See section 13 below for the procedure for approval of interim payments and of settlements.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_3", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.5", "subsection_index": 3, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.6, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.6 A person intending to make a claim may need documents within the control of a likely party to a claim to which they do not yet have access. If the documents are not disclosed voluntarily, in accordance with the Pre-Action Protocols, then CPR31.16 sets out the provisions for making an application for disclosure of documents before proceedings have started. If such an application is made and a claim is later issued, the claim will have a different case number, but the court should be told about the pre-action application and the two cases will be linked on CE file.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_4", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.6", "subsection_index": 4, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.7, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.7 It may also be possible, where proceedings have not yet been started, to make an application for an order for disclosure of documents and information from other sources, who are not likely to be a party to the claim. Pursuant to Norwich Pharmacal v Customs and Excise Commissioners [1974] AC 133 HL, the court may order documents and information to be provided by persons alleged to have been caught up in the wrongs of others. These applications should be made by Part 8 claim form (unless there is a dispute of fact in which case a Part 7 claim form is likely to be appropriate). The application will be placed in the first instance before a Master and will be referred to a High Court judge if the capacity and/or importance of the application warrants it; if the applicant wishes for the application to be dealt with by a High Court Judge, consent from the Master should be sought.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_5", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.7", "subsection_index": 5, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.8, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.8 An application may be made to the court before a claim is brought for the court's assistance in accepting an offer of amends under section 3 of the Defamation Act 1996. The application is made by a Part 8 Claim Form. For more information see section 8 (Part 8 procedure) and section 17 (Media and Communications List) below.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_6", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.8", "subsection_index": 6, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.9, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.9 Permission may be required to serve proceedings or documents out of the jurisdiction. Such applications are made by way of application notice and will usually be dealt with by a Master. The application is usually dealt with on paper. See CPR6.36 to 6.38 and paragraph 6.10 below.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_7", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.9", "subsection_index": 7, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.10, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.10 The applicant must be candid and should draw to the attention of the court in the evidence in support of the application all relevant matters including those which are adverse to the application. A failure to do so may lead to the order giving permission to be struck out.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_8", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.10", "subsection_index": 8, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.11, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.11 Open justice is a fundamental principle of our court system. The general rule is that the names of the parties to a claim are included in all court documents, orders and judgments and hearings are publicly listed with the names of the parties.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_9", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.11", "subsection_index": 9, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.12, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.12 However, the Court does have powers: (a) to permit a Claim Form to be issued without a party's name or address (b) to prevent disclosure of the identity of a claimant or other person; and (c) to prevent or restrict public access to documents on the court file, including statements of case (CPR 5.4C). Such orders will not be made simply because the parties consent. Any departure from the principle of open justice should be the minimum strictly necessary in the interests of justice and for the proper administration of justice. Where the court has permitted a name or other matter to be withheld from the public, the court can impose reporting restrictions under s.ll Contempt of Court Act 1981 prohibiting the publication of that name in connection with the proceedings.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_10", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.12", "subsection_index": 10, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf"}, {"category": "King's Bench Division", "citation": "4.13, 4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41), 35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "content": "4.13 Applications for such orders can be made on issue. Applications should usually be made to a Master. The application should be made at the same time as issuing the claim form and not before. The file will be made private until the application is dealt with. The application should usually be supported by appropriate evidence and a short skeleton argument.", "filepath": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "groups": [], "id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue_subsection_11", "is_subsection": true, "oids": [], "original_doc_id": "4_applications_made_pre_issue_or_at_the_point_of_issue", "reranker_score": 2.6493873596191406, "score": 0.022444169968366623, "sourcefile": "35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "sourcepage": "4. Applications made pre-issue or at the point of issue (p. 41)", "storageUrl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "storageurl": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/35.16_JO_Kings_Bench_Division_Guide_2025_WEB4.pdf", "subsection_id": "4.13", "subsection_index": 11, "total_subsections": 23, "updated": "2025-04-01T00:00:00Z", "url": "https://www.judiciary.uk/wp-content/uploads/202